race.description: Heads To Tails Horseware Maiden Plate
race.comment: Tricky. TEXTURE (5) has had two starts to date. The debut effort at Ballarat was good, not beaten far at Sale last time out. Williams goes aboard and this looks a nice race for him having been tight for room late in that last ruin. BLACK COAL (1) resumes, now with the Bedggood yard. The debut effort here last time in reads well and he can roll forward here to offset the wide gate. Expect he takes catching. CUSHIONED (7) is a filly by Ghaiyyath on debut for the Freedman yard. She draws a soft gate and has jumped out well enough to be a winning factor. CONTOURS (11) was close up on debut here and gets over a bit more ground which will definitely suit.
